---
name: write-instructions
description: Provides guidelines for writing instructions in natural language. Use when writing or editing prompts, rules, commands, skills, or agents.
---

Keep individual instructions as concise and the total number of instructions as low as possible without compromising the overall intent. Aim for at most 20 independent concerns for the given task.

Write instructions for yourself only. Do not include instructions that you would follow regardless of context without being told. If you are unsure whether an instruction is necessary, append "(may be obvious)".

Include examples if they enable an instruction to be more concise or make it clearer.

Prefer verifiable instructions where possible. E.g. "Write at most 50 lines" is verifiable, while "Be brief" is not.

Group instructions by concern. Order concerns by descending importance to the given task.

